title: Mets' 1st playoff lineup in 9 years: Who plays in NLDS Game 1 vs. Los Angeles Dodgers
text:
LOS ANGELES -- For the first time since 2006, the Mets are about to play a postseason game. Now go face Clayton Kershaw.
The Mets have their lineup for Game 1 of the National League Division Series. Jacob deGrom will start. Wilmer Flores and Michael Conforto won't.
First pitch is at 9:45 p.m.
RELATED : How Mets saved their 2015 season and nearly didn't get Yoenis Cespedes in 1 ridiculous week in July
METS
Curtis Granderson - RF David Wright - 3B Yoenis Cespedes - CF Daniel Murphy - 2B Travis d'Arnaud - C Lucas Duda - 1B Michael Cuddyer - LF Ruben Tejada - SS Jacob deGrom - RHP
